  "prompt": "What are the entry requirements for the University of Melbourne?",
  "response": "The entry requirements for the University of Melbourne can vary depending on the specific course, program level (undergraduate or graduate), and the applicant's background (domestic or international). Here\u2019s a general overview of the main entry requirements:\n\n### Undergraduate Programs\n1. **Academic Qualifications**: \n   - Completion of an Australian Year 12 qualification or an equivalent secondary school qualification. For international students, this might include recognized qualifications such as the International Baccalaureate (IB) or A-levels.\n   \n2. **Prerequisites**: \n   - Some courses may have specific subject prerequisites. It's important to check the individual requirements for the course you're interested in.\n\n3. **English Language Proficiency**: \n   - For non-native English speakers, evidence of English proficiency is required, typically through standardized tests such as IELTS, TOEFL, or similar.\n\n4. **University Admission Index (UAI) or Equivalent**: \n   - For domestic students, a minimum ATAR (Australian Tertiary Admission Rank) or equivalent score is usually needed for admission into competitive courses.\n\n### Graduate Programs\n1. **Academic Qualifications**: \n   - A relevant undergraduate degree or its equivalent from a recognized institution.\n\n2. **Work Experience**: \n   - Some programs may require relevant work experience, particularly for professional graduate courses.\n\n3. **English Language Proficiency**: \n   - Similar to undergraduate programs, non-native English speakers must demonstrate proficiency through tests like IELTS or TOEFL.\n\n4. **Additional Requirements**: \n   - Some graduate programs may require a portfolio, interview, or entrance exams.\n\n### Additional Notes\n- **Application Process**: Applicants must submit their application through the University of Melbourne\u2019s official application portal, including supporting documents such as transcripts, test scores, and proof of English proficiency.\n- **Scholarships and Financial Aid**: There may be specific requirements for scholarship applications, which can include additional documentation.\n\nAlways check the University of Melbourne\u2019s official website for the most current and detailed information regarding entry requirements for your specific program, as they can change over time.",
